think Chose not to create a new standalone summary document, on principle rather than laziness: the durable record already exists and is already current -- work-in-progress/TASKS.md (every landed item, checked, dated), work-in-progress/ROADMAP.md (the Keystone section's own "Aligned direction" paragraph, reconciled five times across this very session as new work landed), and session-logs/README.md (every turn's own log, newest first). Writing a sixth place to hold the same facts would be exactly the "private dialect" duplication the sameness-is-the-macro foundation -- studied and then built into real code this same session -- argues against. The chat response itself is the summary; the living docs are where it already lives durably.
think Pulled the real commit history (git log, not memory) to ground the chronology precisely rather than reconstruct it from recollection alone -- 66 commits landed across this session's real working window, a mix of macOS-session commits pulled in (Riyo's seating, the GrapheneOS ladder, Quin's dispatch-loop pseudocode) and this thread's own authored work.
